[1mNAME[0m
       polysort - sort coordinates along a polygon

[1mSYNOPSIS[0m
       [1mpolysort [22m-p polygon_file [-e eps] [-v] [-w] [filename]

[1mDESCRIPTION[0m
       [1mpolysort  [22mis  a program that sorts coordinates using an oriented (i.e.,
       spatially sorted) polygon. It computes the  along-polygon  distance  of
       the  coordinates  from  the first polygon coordinate and uses this dis-
       tance to sort the coordinates. Polysort returns the coordinate numbers.

[1mARGUMENTS[0m
       [1m-p polygon_file[0m
              Oriented polygon used for sorting coordinates. Input consists of
              (x,y)-pairs.

       [1m-e eps [22mNumber to specify precision of coordinate data.

       [1m-v     [22mVerbose  on.   [1m-w  [22mWrapping on. Wrapping is an obscure remainder
              from the past.

       [1mfilename[0m
              File containing coordinates that have to be  ordered  along  the
              polygon. Input consists of node number and (x,y)-pair.

[1mEXAMPLE[0m
       polysort -p Polygon_Eurasia.xy -e 0.01 trench_2
              which  sorts the coordinates in trench_2 given the polygon given
              in Polygon_Eurasia.xy

